HEADWORD: Courap
<hw>Cou*rap"</hw> <pr>(k??-r?p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A skin disease, common in India, in which there is perpetual
itching and eruption, esp. of the groin, breast, armpits, and
face.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

